[Given](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=4d5d66cff30ed477af01f69b11d42115)

```rust
trait T {
    type A: Display;
}

impl T for () {
    type A = ();
}
```

we shouldn't include the last `note` as that is only useful when dealing with expressions:

```
error[E0277]: `()` doesn't implement `std::fmt::Display`
 --> src/lib.rs:8:14
  |
3 | trait T {
  |       - required by a bound in this
4 |     type A: Display;
  |             ------- required by this bound in `T`
...
8 |     type A = ();
  |              ^^ `()` cannot be formatted with the default formatter
  |
  = help: the trait `std::fmt::Display` is not implemented for `()`
  = note: in format strings you may be able to use `{:?}` (or {:#?} for pretty-print) instead
```
